  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To test whether baseline levels of slow wave activity (SWA) during sleep are lower in obese
      adults, and even lower in persons with sleep disordered breathing (SDB) compared to lean
      adults.

      To compare levels of SWA in individuals in relation to their sleep time, blood pressure,
      heart rate, and markers of glucose metabolism.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
